Pandas library is used to perform DataFrame operations¶

In [240]:

     'FirstName':['Priya','Jiya','Niya','Riya'],
     'LastName':['Varma','Sharma','More','Patil'],
     'Department':['HR','Accounts','Engg','Pharmacy'],
     'Salary':[50000,20000,40000,30000]}

Rows subsetting¶

  1. df.iloc[row_index , column_index]
  2. df.loc[row_name , column_name] ~if u want all the columns = df.iloc[row_index , :] ~ if u want to slice only rows = df.loc[row_name , :]

if u want from index 4 to index 9¶

####Remember
###In loc function exact value is given (step) is not used here-- for eg. 4 to 9 ```It will display all 4 to 9 rows 
###But in iloc function (step) is used
###In iloc (i) stands for internal numbering , and loc says direct numbering
D.loc[1:9,['RND','MKT']]

###another method to perform above sum is :-----
###add round brakets for OR function as u used above
###other 2 methods are below
fil1=A['PROFIT']>=80000
fil2=A['PROFIT']<=100000
fil3=A['STATE']=='Florida'
fil4=A['STATE']=='New York'
fil = fil1 & fil2 & (fil3 | fil4)

Sort the data according to price¶

Sorting means arranging data in ascending or descending order

~1. Text - A-Z or Z-A ~2. Numeric columns - arrange according to numbers
